    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Oil Pan and Oil Suction Tube -
        Clean and Inspect
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Clean and Inspect</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove RTV sealant from the crankcase, oil pan, front cover, and flywheel housing mating
                    surfaces with a flat scraper. Scrape parallel to the gasket path.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the oil pan, front cover, flywheel housing, oil suction tube assembly, and
                    crankcase mating surfaces thoroughly with a suitable solvent.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and inspect the oil pan gasket. Discard the oil pan gasket if it is cracked or the
                    sealing surfaces are damaged.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and inspect the oil suction tube assembly. Make sure the oil suction tube is free
                    of obstructions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the oil pan and oil suction tube assembly for cracks and damage. Replace
                    components if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
